138
00:07:30,286 --> 00:07:32,286
Now I have to believe it.

139
00:07:32,286 --> 00:07:35,286
We have to practice harder. It has to get better.

140
00:07:35,286 --> 00:07:38,286
One, two. One, two.

141
00:07:45,134 --> 00:07:48,134
Ghost, come on, you should have some too!

142
00:07:57,134 --> 00:08:00,134
What do you say to that?

143
00:08:00,174 --> 00:08:05,174
We're just getting started with the practice and you're already making such
progress?

144
00:08:05,174 --> 00:08:09,174
Clara, I'm happy. Together we can do it.

145
00:08:09,174 --> 00:08:12,174
Yes, now I know it too.

146
00:08:19,174 --> 00:08:21,174
Is Clara already gone?

147
00:08:21,174 --> 00:08:23,174
Good evening, Peter, good evening!

148
00:08:23,174 --> 00:08:26,030
Go, say quickly, have you already got up?

149
00:08:26,030 --> 00:08:29,030
No, not yet. That would be too early.

150
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:31,030
What? Why?

151
00:08:31,030 --> 00:08:34,030
Now don't be so disappointed. I can show you something else.

152
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:37,030
Pay attention. Here.

153
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:43,030
Yes, tell me, Clara. You can move.

154
00:08:43,030 --> 00:08:45,940
All of a sudden it went all by itself. Right, Heidi?

155
00:08:45,940 --> 00:08:48,940
Yes, tonight we have to write a letter to the grandmother.

156
00:08:48,940 --> 00:08:50,940
She must know that you can move her.

157
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:53,940
Yes, and you'll give it to her tomorrow at the post office.

158
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:56,940
Huh? Oh, Heidi.

159
00:08:58,940 --> 00:08:59,940
Oh.

160
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:02,940
Heidi, a big kiss, please!

161
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:04,940
Yes, of course, we'll do that.

162
00:09:35,684 --> 00:09:41,684
It's getting better and better!

163
00:09:42,184 --> 00:09:45,184
Slowly, one more piece, come on!

164
00:09:54,184 --> 00:09:56,184
So...

165
00:10:06,184 --> 00:10:08,184
Can you run now?

166
00:10:08,424 --> 00:10:11,424
Now tell me, Clara, quickly, have you already walked today?

167
00:10:11,424 --> 00:10:14,424
No, not yet, but almost. It won't take long.

168
00:10:14,424 --> 00:10:17,424
Today I would have sworn that you can do it.

169
00:10:17,424 --> 00:10:19,424
Well?

170
00:10:19,424 --> 00:10:21,424
Oh, the letters. There, they are for you.

171
00:10:21,424 --> 00:10:24,424
You didn't get them upstairs in the garden, did you?

172
00:10:24,424 --> 00:10:27,424
Of course not, I forgot them again this morning.

173
00:10:27,424 --> 00:10:30,424
I thought of the grandmother. There, Clara.

174
00:10:30,424 --> 00:10:31,424
Thank you.

175
00:10:31,424 --> 00:10:34,424
But now I'm curious.

176
00:10:34,424 --> 00:10:37,424
I'm afraid I won't be able to help you.

177
00:10:37,424 --> 00:10:37,736
You're welcome.

178
00:10:37,736 --> 00:10:43,136
Dear Heidi, thank you so much for helping Clara practice every day.

179
00:10:43,136 --> 00:10:47,536
I'm thinking about you and I'm trying to imagine what you're doing.

180
00:10:47,536 --> 00:10:50,936
The sanatorium I'm in is very nice.

181
00:10:50,936 --> 00:10:54,736
When I look out the window, I see the mountains right in front of me.

182
00:10:54,736 --> 00:10:58,136
And then I know that somewhere up there are my two children

183
00:10:58,136 --> 00:11:02,136
and that at some point Clara will learn to walk up there.

184
00:11:02,136 --> 00:11:07,336
I had a dream the other day. I saw how Clara walked across the meadow and was
faster than you, Heidi.

185
00:11:07,486 --> 00:11:10,986
Did you hear what I just read? She dreamed that you could walk!

186
00:11:10,986 --> 00:11:12,986
Leave me alone!

187
00:11:12,986 --> 00:11:15,986
All of you are waiting for me to finally be able to walk!

188
00:11:15,986 --> 00:11:17,986
And what if I can't?

189
00:11:17,986 --> 00:11:19,986
But Clara...

190
00:11:19,986 --> 00:11:23,986
I want to tell you something. It doesn't matter to me if I ever walk.

191
00:11:23,986 --> 00:11:25,486
But...

192
00:11:25,486 --> 00:11:27,486
Stop crying.

193
00:11:27,486 --> 00:11:29,486
Clara, you will be able to walk.

194
00:11:31,486 --> 00:11:33,486
I don't want to walk anymore.

195
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:36,986
I don't care anymore.

196
00:11:37,986 --> 00:11:40,486
I don't want to practice anymore.

197
00:11:42,486 --> 00:11:45,486
I just want you to finally leave me alone.

198
00:11:47,986 --> 00:11:51,486
And I don't want Peter to ask me every night.

199
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:10,890
Clara, it's okay. Maybe they're all too impatient. You're right.

200
00:12:10,890 --> 00:12:16,890
We will give you more time. Peter doesn't ask anymore and Heidi doesn't push
anymore.

201
00:12:16,890 --> 00:12:20,890
We wish it for you. Nobody wanted to hurt you.

202
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:22,890
I'm sorry. Me too.

203
00:12:22,890 --> 00:12:25,890
If I did something wrong, I'm sorry. Me too.

204
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:27,890
I'm sorry, please.

205
00:12:29,442 --> 00:12:34,442
I'm sorry, Grandfather. I can't go on like this.

206
00:12:34,442 --> 00:12:38,442
I give up. I want to go back to Frankfurt.

207
00:12:38,442 --> 00:12:40,442
Good.

208
00:12:58,370 --> 00:13:03,370
Before we started our sound exercises, you couldn't even move your legs.

209
00:13:05,370 --> 00:13:07,370
And now you can.

210
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:10,370
Is that right or am I saying something wrong?

211
00:13:10,370 --> 00:13:12,370
Now say something, Clara.

212
00:13:13,370 --> 00:13:14,370
It's right.

213
00:13:14,370 --> 00:13:16,370
You see.

214
00:13:17,370 --> 00:13:20,370
In the beginning you thought it was going very fast.

215
00:13:20,370 --> 00:13:23,370
You just have to practice a little bit, nothing more.

216
00:13:23,370 --> 00:13:26,370
And now all of a sudden you see that it's not going the way you think.

217
00:13:26,792 --> 00:13:32,792
That makes you impatient and makes you doubt, because you didn't believe in the
effectiveness of the exercise from the start.

218
00:13:33,792 --> 00:13:37,792
How do you know? I really didn't believe in the exercises.

219
00:13:39,792 --> 00:13:43,792
Every time I wanted something from you, you saw it.

220
00:13:44,792 --> 00:13:48,792
Clara, I know you in the meantime. You lose your temper so easily.

221
00:13:50,792 --> 00:13:55,792
You know, I won't take one from you. I don't think you really want to go back to
Frankfurt so quickly.

222
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,680
I don't think you're that weak and cowardly.

223
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:01,680
Of course you want to be able to walk, but you can't walk fast enough.

224
00:14:01,680 --> 00:14:03,680
And that's why you're crying.

225
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,680
No, not because of that!

226
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:20,290
Ungrateful people can not run and will never be able to live in it.

227
00:14:20,290 --> 00:14:25,290
Fortunately, you don't have to listen to him, because you can run if you want.

228
00:14:25,290 --> 00:14:28,290
It shouldn't matter how long it takes.

229
00:14:28,290 --> 00:14:33,290
Tell me, isn't the main thing to know that you learn it one day?

230
00:14:37,290 --> 00:14:41,290
I'm sorry. I don't know what happened to me.

231
00:14:41,290 --> 00:14:43,290
Somehow the courage was gone.

232
00:14:44,184 --> 00:14:47,184
Hm, I knew it would come.

233
00:14:48,184 --> 00:14:51,184
Ah, Clara, what a beautiful sunset.

234
00:14:52,184 --> 00:14:54,184
Yes.

235
00:14:58,588 --> 00:15:01,588
I don't understand anything anymore.

236
00:15:17,756 --> 00:15:22,756
