256
00:16:56,620 --> 00:17:00,620
Now I haven't been up here for years and everything is still as it was.

257
00:17:06,620 --> 00:17:09,404
Heidi! Clara!

258
00:17:09,404 --> 00:17:13,404
I picked them for you, because you must be busy again today.

259
00:17:13,404 --> 00:17:15,404
Thank you, Peter, that's nice of you.

260
00:17:15,404 --> 00:17:17,404
Nice, thank you.

261
00:17:17,404 --> 00:17:19,404
I don't care and I don't ask.

262
00:17:19,404 --> 00:17:21,404
Yes, today you can ask.

263
00:17:21,404 --> 00:17:23,404
He can, right?

264
00:17:23,404 --> 00:17:25,404
Yes, it's getting better and better.

265
00:17:25,404 --> 00:17:27,404
That makes me happy. Keep practicing, okay?

266
00:17:27,404 --> 00:17:29,404
Oh dear.

267
00:17:31,404 --> 00:17:33,404
What happened to her?

268
00:17:33,404 --> 00:17:35,404
Come on, let's see what's going on.

269
00:17:35,404 --> 00:17:37,404
Oh dear.

270
00:17:37,404 --> 00:17:38,674
Oh dear.

271
00:17:38,674 --> 00:17:41,674
So don't stand around, make sure I get rid of the goats.

272
00:17:41,674 --> 00:17:44,674
I can't do anything about it, they ran away on their own.

273
00:17:44,674 --> 00:17:46,674
Watch out that I get rid of them.

274
00:17:46,674 --> 00:17:49,674
Get lost, make sure you get away, go!

275
00:17:49,674 --> 00:17:52,674
What about the goats, they've never done that before.

276
00:17:52,674 --> 00:17:57,674
Nothing special, I've collected their favorite herbs and they smell good.

277
00:17:57,674 --> 00:17:59,674
And do you want to give them to Swain?

278
00:17:59,674 --> 00:18:02,674
Of course, their milk has to be just as good as Geislein's.

279
00:18:02,674 --> 00:18:04,636
Now go.

280
00:18:04,636 --> 00:18:05,636
All for me.

281
00:18:05,636 --> 00:18:07,636
I can't just take them away.

282
00:18:07,636 --> 00:18:09,636
What am I supposed to do?

283
00:18:10,636 --> 00:18:12,636
They don't listen to me anymore.

284
00:18:12,636 --> 00:18:16,636
If I don't want to stay in here all night, I'll have to come up with something.

285
00:18:16,636 --> 00:18:18,636
Joseph!

286
00:18:18,636 --> 00:18:20,636
Come here!

287
00:18:21,506 --> 00:18:23,506
Come back!

288
00:18:23,506 --> 00:18:25,506
Come back!

289
00:18:29,506 --> 00:18:31,506
Come back!

290
00:18:31,506 --> 00:18:33,506
Come back!

291
00:18:35,506 --> 00:18:37,506
Good job, Joseph!

292
00:18:37,506 --> 00:18:39,506
Stop it! Not again!

293
00:18:39,506 --> 00:18:41,506
Not again!

294
00:18:41,506 --> 00:18:43,506
Not again!

295
00:18:43,506 --> 00:18:45,506
Goodbye, you two!

296
00:18:45,506 --> 00:18:47,506
Goodbye!

297
00:18:47,506 --> 00:18:49,506
Goodbye!

298
00:18:49,506 --> 00:18:51,506
To be continued

299
00:18:58,230 --> 00:19:01,230
The goats are fed, now we have to take care of our food.

300
00:19:01,230 --> 00:19:03,230
They're hungry.

301
00:19:04,230 --> 00:19:08,230
You did all this for me. You looked for the herbs for me.

302
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:11,230
Who eats the herbs, you or Swenli?

303
00:19:11,230 --> 00:19:13,230
Grandfather, you mean...

304
00:19:14,230 --> 00:19:15,230
You mean...

305
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:29,230
You mean...

306
00:19:34,230 --> 00:19:34,422
You mean...

307
00:19:34,422 --> 00:19:37,422
I've already written a lot more than you. Come on, show me!

308
00:19:37,422 --> 00:19:39,422
Oh, stop it! That's mean! Give it to me!

309
00:19:39,422 --> 00:19:44,422
No, Heidi, give me the letter! It doesn't matter what I've written! Give it to
me!

310
00:19:44,422 --> 00:19:49,422
Heidi, give it to me! If you don't stop, I'll read your letter! Give it to me!

311
00:19:49,422 --> 00:19:50,422
Heidi!

312
00:19:50,614 --> 00:19:51,614
Please don't.

313
00:19:51,614 --> 00:19:54,614
If you read my letter, I can read what you wrote.

314
00:19:54,614 --> 00:19:55,614
Good.

315
00:19:55,614 --> 00:19:56,614
There you have it.

316
00:19:56,614 --> 00:19:57,614
Here.

317
00:20:20,614 --> 00:20:21,614
Bye.

318
00:20:21,614 --> 00:20:22,614
Bye.

319
00:20:22,614 --> 00:20:23,614
Bye.

320
00:20:23,614 --> 00:20:24,614
Bye.

321
00:20:24,614 --> 00:20:25,430
Bye.

322
00:20:25,430 --> 00:20:28,430
Let go of my hands, then I'll fall over.

323
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:30,830
Now!

324
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:35,430
That's not how it works. You just have to forget that you have arms

325
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:38,230
and just think that your legs are supposed to carry you.

326
00:20:38,430 --> 00:20:41,430
You're good, I've been trying all this time.

327
00:20:44,830 --> 00:20:45,830
Good, go on!

328
00:20:46,830 --> 00:20:48,310
Clara, and?

329
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:50,310
Did it hurt?

330
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:53,310
Not the legs, but the hand. I fell on it.

331
00:20:53,310 --> 00:20:55,310
Doesn't even sound like it.

332
00:20:55,310 --> 00:20:58,310
Probably just a little stung. Come on, let's keep going.

333
00:20:58,310 --> 00:20:59,310
Don't be a frog.

334
00:20:59,310 --> 00:21:03,310
Oh, stop it. That has nothing to do with it. I don't feel like it anymore today.

335
00:21:04,310 --> 00:21:07,310
When will you all finally realize that it doesn't make sense?

336
00:21:07,310 --> 00:21:09,310
I'll never be able to walk. Never.

337
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:12,310
Stop complaining!

338
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:15,310
I can't hear it anymore.

339
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:19,750
All the time you say you can't do it. You don't want to do it at all.

340
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:23,750
And all the time you shout that your legs don't want to carry you.

341
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:28,750
Your legs are fine, do you hear? You just don't want your legs to carry you.

342
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:32,750
Because you don't want to be able to walk at all, Clara.

343
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:35,750
No, Heidi, don't wake me up. Stay here.

344
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:39,750
No, I don't even think about it. Heidi!

345
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:45,750
This can't be happening.

346
00:21:49,648 --> 00:21:54,448
A little more wobbly, but I'm standing on my own two legs.

347
00:21:54,448 --> 00:21:56,248
She can do it all at once.

348
00:21:56,248 --> 00:21:59,048
It can't be, I don't believe it.

349
00:22:04,848 --> 00:22:06,848
Hold on!

350
00:22:08,648 --> 00:22:10,648
Heidi!

351
00:22:11,848 --> 00:22:13,848
I'll hold you, be careful, Clara.

352
00:22:13,848 --> 00:22:15,376
We did it.

353
00:22:15,376 --> 00:22:18,616
Yes, it looks like it, but maybe I'm just dreaming.

354
00:22:18,616 --> 00:22:20,616
No! You're not dreaming!

355
00:22:28,876 --> 00:22:32,876
We did it! We did it! We did it!

356
00:22:43,632 --> 00:22:48,632
When Peter came up to the Alps the next morning, he didn't dare to look at it at
first.

357
00:22:48,632 --> 00:22:53,632
But then, when he finally understood what had happened, he was overjoyed.

358
00:22:53,632 --> 00:22:56,632
Heidi and Clara practiced running every day from now on.

359
00:22:56,632 --> 00:23:01,632
And every day went a little better, Clara was able to go a little further.

360
00:23:01,632 --> 00:23:05,632
First still supported by Heidi and later even a few steps alone.

361
00:23:05,632 --> 00:23:11,632
But Clara still didn't want to believe that she could finally run.

362
00:23:12,038 --> 00:23:17,038
And when the bad luck with the wheelchair happened, it was unbearable.

363
00:23:17,038 --> 00:23:21,038
But we want to tell you about it in our next story.

364
00:23:21,468 --> 00:23:29,468
Heidi, Heidi, your world are the mountains.

365
00:23:29,468 --> 00:23:37,468
Heidi, Heidi, because up here you are at home.

366
00:23:37,468 --> 00:23:43,468
Heidi, Heidi, come home.

367
00:23:43,468 --> 00:23:50,468
Find your happiness, come back home.

368
00:23:51,468 --> 00:23:53,040
To be continued

